## Rule 6: Telegram Notification (Thread Routing)

### 6.1 Notification Trigger Points

**Thread 718:** PR merged → main, feature released, Master Doc updated
**Thread 727:** Design completed, FE implemented, BE implemented, dev blocked
**Thread 735:** Pre-commit tests done, automated tests done, QA pass/fail

### 6.2 Sending Notification

```bash
# Thread 727 — Design/Dev report
node scripts/send-dev-report.js \
  --agent "<agent-name>" --feature "<feature-name>" \
  --status "completed|blocked|failed" \
  --message "<report-content>" --thread "727"

# Thread 735 — Test report
node test-pre-commit.js --telegram --thread "735"

# Thread 718 — Changelog
node scripts/send-changelog.js \
  --title "Brief Summary" --category "feature|fix|security|deployment|breaking" \
  --changes "Change 1\nChange 2\nChange 3" --thread "718"
```

