## Rule 8: Error Handling & Escalation

### 8.1 Failure Modes

| Failure Type | Action |
|--------------|--------|
| Cannot read doc | Report Thread 727 → ❌ Failed |
| Build fails | Attempt fix 3x → report → ❌ Failed |
| Design rejected | Wait for user feedback → ⏸️ Blocked |
| Test failures | Log bugs → report severity → ⚠️/❌ |

### 8.2 QA FAIL Workflow

```
1. Log all bugs → Create GitHub issues with severity
2. Update QA Doc → Add bug reports + changelog
3. Report to USER:
   - Bug list with severity
   - Options: Fix & re-test / Deploy with known issues / Rollback
4. WAIT for user decision — do NOT proceed
```

---

## Rule 9: Changelog Synchronization

### 9.1 Each Subagent Updates its own Doc changelog

| Subagent | Updates | Reports To |
|----------|---------|------------|
| Product-Designer | Product Doc changelog | Thread 727 |
| Frontend-Developer | Engineering Doc changelog (FE) | Thread 727 |
| Backend-Developer | Engineering Doc changelog (BE) | Thread 727 |
| QA-Tester | QA Doc changelog | Thread 735 |

### 9.2 Master Doc Aggregation

Master Doc aggregates all subagent changelogs. When all complete & QA PASS:
```bash
node scripts/send-changelog.js \
  --title "Feature <name> completed" \
  --category "feature" \
  --changes "Design completed\nFrontend implemented\nBackend implemented\nQA passed" \
  --thread "718"
```

